<h2>Have they been defeated?</h2>
<p>What is being hailed as <a href="https://www.thesun.co.uk/news/8401087/isis-battle-wipe-off-earth-terror-fall-hours/">the &#8220;final battle&#8221;</a> against ISIS is set to clear the village of Baghouz in Syria on February 11.</p>
<p>Fighters supported by British and US special forces are closing in on the kill.</p>
<p>The Kurdish-led Syrian Democratic Forces, with help from British and US special forces, have advanced over the area in the past few days.</p>
<p>US-led coalition drones are helping troops on the ground by giving a top-down perspective of the battle to commadners.</p>
<p>Warplanes have been dropping huge bombs after being called in by SDF troops, according to reports.</p>
<p>SDF spokesman Mustafa Bali said: &#8220;We will launch an attack to end the Daesh (ISIS) presence or they will turn themselves in.</p>
<p>“There are no other options for them. We confirm there are no negotiations and no intention to have negotiations.”</p>
<figure class="article__media">
	<div class="article__media-img-container open-gallery" data-index="4">

		<a href="#"><p><img class="wp-image-8401645 size-thesun-article-image" src="https://www.thesun.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/AF-MAP-FALL-CALLIPHATE-2.jpg?strip=all&amp;w=750&quality=100" alt="How times of changed... ISIS control has waned away into nothing " width="750" height="500" /></p></a>

		
				<div class="article__gallery-count theme__background-color-rgba-80">
			<a href=""><span class="article__gallery-count-value theme__copy-color">5</span></a>
		</div>
			</div>

		<figcaption class="article__media-caption">
		How times of changed&#8230; ISIS control has waned away into nothing	</figcaption>
	</figure>

